caption: Great Thai food at an amazing price - their lunch special is a steal for the price!
I dumped most of the takeout to the trash can. 🤢
Best Thai food of all the Thai stores by us

Delicious food at a reasonable price! This is my first time ordering from this restaurant, of course as takeout. I have to say I'm not only impressed with the price, but the quality of food is superb. I ordered tofu pad see-ew, egg rolls, and spring rolls and am very satisfied with everything I got. The spring rolls were not what I was expecting - they put their own twist on them and they were great! Would definitely recommend this restaurant - they're now my to go Thai place!
Best Thai food around!!! The spicy basil and pad khe mao are amazing! Staff is great as well
Pho's is my favorite Thai place in the city.  Their food is affordable and sensationally flavorful.  Before you decide on your favorite Thai place, try Pho's.

No thanks needed!, simply the best Thai food I've had in Chicago. I've been to all 3 locations and this for some reason always taste best. Hands down my top Thai restaurant in the US! (lived in 28 different states, no one can come close to Pho's pad thai.) spice level 4 with a side of peanut sauce. 😌 🤪
Delicious pad see ew and basil fried rice.
Phenomenal food every time
So good
Would drive an hour just for their cucumber salad.

Got this for New Year’s Eve! If you love spicy this is the place for you! A bang for you buck as well! Dinner and lunch for the next day :) will definitely be getting weekly take out from here! (Staff is so friendly and nice as well!!!) :) thanks for great service and food!
This place is delicious! We got the lunch special- which is a great deal- very good portions! I got the pad kee mao with tofu. It was so flavorful, the veggies taste very fresh and tofu was perfect.
I walked in and saw some gross things. Better clean
If You love spicy food  this place will get you

My boyfriend and I always get the Pad Thai with Tofu and Pineapple Fried Rice with veggies which is delicious with raisins, cashews! It’s unique and haven’t found that same fried rice other places. We have been going for two years every time we have a craving for Thai Food. We have checked out other places when we have cravings yet it doesn’t fulfill the craving. Therefore we always return to Pho’s to get our cravings in.
This is my favorite Thai place in Chicago! My favorites are the red chicken curry, satay chicken, cucumber salad, and chicken pho. It’s amazing every time!

I Have been here before multiple times. Today I happen to be sober enough to leave a review. If you’re looking for fat spicy Thai noodles topped with heavenly tasting vegetables and proteins, stop driving. (Or looking for an Uber) Walk in here and indulge your 5 senses with any of the signature platters they have to offer. Be careful with the spice levels, you may find yourself tearing and sneezing 🔥
Dope Thai food!!!
Straight up the best Thai in the city. Every dish I’ve had hits it out of the park. Particularly the panang curry! Just be careful with the spice!
The place offers a great variety of delicious food. I like dining here. Employees are always very kind, rates are affordable and the place is always kept clean.

Delicious! My boyfriend and I can love spicy food so we ordered medium spice Pad Thai and Pad Bai Grapraow and it did not disappoint! It had significant heat but was so delicious we couldn’t stop eating it.
Best place for some heat in your food!!! Lunch specials are priced just right for the amount of food you get. (Which is a lot!)

I love Thai food. I’ve had a lot of different Thai food. THIS is the place to go hands down, delicious entrees that are very flavorful. I moved further away from the location and I still order from here. Nothing has compared.
Favorite Thai place in Chicago! Their Panang Curry Beef is so tasteful. I’ve tried just about every Panang Curry in the city, but I always end up back here. Love the spiciness

Delivery. The first time the food was really good. The next time I have no idea what happened. Did you change cooks this week? Im pretty sure these were leftover noodles from the previous day as they were way too soggy. Omg it was totally different and had a ton of sprouts in both dishes I ordered. Crazy. It is like someone just threw a bunch in there to annoy the customers. I ordered pad thai and pad see ew and both were infested with sprouts. Also the carrots are too much as well. The noodles were soggy this time around and the food was just wasn't tasty. The cook got lazy or this was reheated noodles. Very disappointed in this food. I thought I had found a new Thai place but I guess not.
Favorite Thai place in the city
Everything is top notch - but the Tom Ka soup is the reason we happily drive 20 minutes to get here!!! One of the only restaurants I would actively recommend someone seek out!
The lunch deal is truly unbeatable and consistently great!
I have been ordering from this place at least once a week. I absolutely love it! All the dishes that I have tried are delicious. Wish they sold smoothies (= other than that best place in the area!
The food was awesome, especially the fried rice. Its totally worth the visit
Good value for the price.
Absolutely delicious! Lots of flavor and spice!

This place is decent in a pinch, plus they have this kitschy rating system defining how spicy to prepare your food. If you order with the hottest rating, they will take your picture and put it on the wall. Fun. The indoor seating is very limited. I would guess the entire place is 1,000 square feet. It feels grimy and old inside, but in a way that they manage to pull off giving it character. Unfortunately, the overall quality of the food is just average. They need to step up the quality of the ingredients in my opinion.
Very good
so much good food for a great price. can’t wait to eat here again
bestThai restaurant ever. live super close and never disappoints. 11/10 would definitely recommend. Get Pad see ew!!!
My new favorite place!!! I am so happy to have found this place. Everything was absolutely delicious. Well cooked, tasty and very reasonable prices. Definitely recommend this place

Ordered the panang curry last night and it was delicious. Also got the chicken satay which was such a large helping of the peanut sauce and chicken that I ate if for leftovers today. Delicious! I got the Thai custard which was really good as well. This is my favorite new Thai place! Will continue ordering(:
Have ordered this delivered several times, excellent quality, value, and great portions. Would recommend to anyone, be aware their warnings about spicy items should be considered seriously.

Ordered takeout from here last night and was very pleased. Got the cucumber salad, fried rice, pad thai, and pho. It was very tasty and I was happy with the portion size - it was like 2 full means so I had my leftovers for lunch. Thankful they are open during this difficult time and making great food.

My family and I came to love mama and my entire family was impressed by the quality of food served at this restaurant. The restaurant had a small outdoors patio and the service was fast. We got the Thai Red Curry, vegetarian curry pot, and the mix seafood curry lacks. We left satisfied and made plans to return.  I definitely recommend this place :).
The meals and service were beyond our expectations. We truly liked the atmosphere of this restaurant. Nice place to take the family out for dinner.
Nice food. Service is ok.
This spot clearly knows how to take care of their clients. Always with a nice demeanor. The food is reasonably priced, constantly delightful and clean.
Panang curry is to d i e for
Great Nam Tuk. And best Crab Rangoon and sauce ever!

I ordered Pad Phed. "Spicy?" - "Mild, please." Soon after, a nice smiling lady brings out the food, I taste it, and it's super spicy! Waiter comes over: "How is everything?" - "It's very spicy!" ... And the waiter smiles and WALKS AWAY! I chose to try to eat some of the rice anyways because I was very hungry and pressed for time. At the end, as the waiter brought my check: "Would you like it to go?" - "No, I didn't like it, it was too spicy, I can't eat it."...  And once again, the waiter smiles and WALKS AWAY!!! Everyone is friendly and smiling but NO solution was offered. No apology, no offering a substitute - nothing! I paid my bill - in full - and left. Why 2 stars and not 1? Thai iced coffee was pretty good.
Hottest food challenge in Chicago!  Free food and photo on the wall

Love this place! Great prices and great food! Love the flavor (although I never get anything spicy...)  I absolutely adore the vibe here. It's so small it's quite literally a hole in the wall but it's so cozy and quaint.
Would surely recommend trying out this place. Excellent vibes, yummy food, good service. Great work.
AMAZING!  Some of the very best Thai in Chicago.  Wings, Pad Kee Mao, Curry were all amazing.  Unique flavor and non of it is too heavy.  Fresh ingredients.  Definitely planning to become a regular.
Delicious vegetarian Pad Thai. Extremely spicy. Just perfect
Really spicy and really delicious

Really really bad. Pad Thai was made with sweet and sour sauce and missing key components. The beef tasted like dogfood. Service was lacking even with very modest expectations. Was able to get the noodles comped after some hassling and a call to the owner. Ownership was surprised to hear that their "famous pad Thai" was returned.  This place is not authentic and not good.  The gimmick here is getting your food as spicy as possible in order to win the prize of getting your picture on the wall.  As fun as that sounds, I won't be back.
Great food and very reasonably priced.

The best pho in Lakeview!  Cute little shop, very intimate, cozy, and affordable.  The lunch special is a great deal, but I prefer to get the beef pho.  For only $8, you get a huge bowl and you get to customize your spiciness for each dish.  I don't mind spicy food at all but even the mild plus level is hard for me.  If you are a spiciness connoisseur you can try the extra hot!  Last time I was in, I saw a visitor get 20x extra hot and he started sweating immediately (so be warned!). Also the egg rolls are amazing, the staff is nice. My only complaint is that the smoothies aren't offered at this location. Hopefully in the future!  Also be warned there is not a bathroom.
Awesome spot to get food when in a hurry. Their customer service is quick, rates are reasonable, awesome character. Will visit here again
Easily the spiciest food I've ever had. By far.
Bad service but decent food for the price
Good, tried the chicken basil fried chicken. Hot, don't underestimate, their hot is pretty hot. Can't imagine 5X. Thai iced tea is good too!
Tom Kah was good
Solid Thai
Great food and friendly staff. Quaint, affordable little date spot.
Amazing Thai food at great prices! Be careful if you try the challange
Authentic and super spicy, if you’re weak get less than the mild 😂
Reasonable prices, good food
Love this place! They have the best lunch deal- I always get the shrimp green curry, which has a lot of veggies, too.  Great price, great food, great atmosphere and service.
Very satisfied w/ food. Not expensive either
Went on a friend’s recommendation. The food is delicious and the menu has a wide variety.
The food was delicious and the staff friendly. Trust their spiciness scale, it is hotter than most Thai restaurants.
Outstanding food and presentation. This place is exemplary of small, awesome Chicago food joints.
Small restaurant with only a few tables, family owned, not fancy but good food at a great price.
Very, very spicy Thai food. The appetizers were not particularly remarkable, though I do not regret getting the potstickers. And remember that panang is king!
Great food
Great Thai food
Great little gem and terrific prices

Food is great. The place is small and it's BYOB. Warning, even the mild is spicy, so if you can't handle spicy and I would suggest to get the pad thai. The Penang is awesome, as are all the curry dishes. The prices are very reasonable and the service is very fast and fresh.
If you like your food with a kick, Pho's menu is the Jean Claude Van Damme of Thai food.  I always get the papaya salad with my orders.
Love the food as always. Try it with some heat.

Very pleasantly surprised with the unique offerings at Pho's Thai Cuisine.  There were lots of things on the menu here that i don't normally see at Thai restaurants (mushroom terrine with rice crackers, sour soup with an omelette on top) and I'm glad I tried it. I didn't have a reservation and the wait ended up being around 45 minutes, so plan ahead. It's around the corner from the mall so you can walk around while you wait (they'll text you). I would definitely come back to try more things.

Oh jeeze. I thought I was cool the first time I went here and got regular spicy. Please if you think you like spicy go for medium. I brought my leftovers to work and gave it to some cooks in the kitchen who try to mess with my taste buds and they were crying. I cant believe theres someone on that wall that did 15x spicy. I'm positive his butt hole melted.

A bit disappointed. I hadn't ordered from here in years. I let them  "scare" me by telling me the medium Tom Yum "is hot". No other restaurant has ever warned me about  Tom Yum soup! So, I figured that must mean their's is a lot hotter than normal, and so I took mild. Bad decision! No flavor, no spice whatsoever!! Just sweet. Big disappointment especially as I picked it up to burn a cold out of me today. Same darn thing w/ noodle dish- pad Khe ma. Please, Pho's don't warn about heat when your menu says it's spicy, and classically it's supposed to have some heat- we know we're ordering a spicy dish. This again in "mild" had NO SPICE at all. 😩 Very happily surprised though by the three free crab Rangoon in my bag, that were absolutely delicious! One of the best I've had! Just wish I knew they were in there, as I didn't go straight home so I didn't eat them till later when they were getting cool. I will go back for some of those again though.
Love this places great I still don’t have the courage to try hot but still great food.
(Translated by Google) Good place to eat hot wings  (Original) Buen lugar para comer hot wings
Spicy chicken salad and curry were delicious!
Best Thai food in the city!
Love the spicy food....they got hell lot of spicy levels.....and you can be on theirs wall of fame if you can have their top level spicy dishes......
Great food!!
Careful!! We found 4 staples in our chicken vegetable soup. Almost swallowed it but I have to say thank God my daughter didn't eat this. Could be a costly mistake for the business.
Best Thai food in the city, hands down! You won’t find a better Pad Khee Mao anywhere outside of Thailand.  Making his Aunt & Uncle proud!
The hot Pho is face melting & delicious. Service is exceptional. Love this place!
My favorite thai spot.
Good food very consistently. If you order delivery through them they have some pretty good discounts as opposed to Grubhub or door dash.
Food is disgusting my pad Thai was watery and noodles weren’t cooked all the way. A huge disappointment
Tasted fresh, reasonable price, nice atmosphere.
Very good food!

Holy cannoli this place was spicy. Some body should of hired the Fire Brigade when I visited. I legit have never had spicer food and I ordered mild plus. Let’s just say the bathroom at work will be ocupado for quite some time tomorrow.
(Translated by Google) Delicious  (Original) Delicioso

Obsessed with this place! Love the homemade crab Rangoon’s. The red curry is Amazing! Also the mild Plus is the perfect amount of spice. The medium is way to much and I loveee spicy. Just not when my nose is running the entire time. I’ve had the almost everything on the menu! You can’t go wrong!
Great, cheap Thai food
Very willing to customize for vegetarians. Food was quite tasty.

The food is good. Most curries will have a sweet taste to it. If you like that you will like all thr curries. I prefer savory food and do not really like my food to be sweet. Which limits my options. But other than that all dishes taste great! We got a dessert called "lichee on ice" and funny enough we got literally that. Lichees and ice cubes in a bowl. And yes that in no way sounds like a dessert you would expect at a restaurant but I enjoyed it nonetheles. I just love them lichees.
Family-owned very fresh and very well made excellent Thai food. I have known the family for 15 years.
Amazing food, 10/10 would recommend
They have the spuciest Thai food you'll ever have here!
Food was excellent, as good of Thai food that you can find in the area. Will be back and would recommend.
Excellent meal, the papaya salad is very tasty, love the fresh garlic. The curry was very good, should have gotten a bit more spice.
Tasted good, very fast service. Reminds me of the hole-in-the-wall cafes in Vietnam and Thailand. They will go spicy if asked 👍

Wow...Bad. Pad Thai had a very rancid smell and taste, like something spoiled. Panang curry was equally bad. Brown and really thick, not fresh No coconut milk as far as we could tell. At least the egg rolls were ok and the waiter agreed not to charge us. We eat out a lot, never felt motivated to write a bad review until today.
Great food and gives a challenge to all spicy food lovers. Eat any dish x5 hot and you get it free with a picture on the wall. Not fit for the faint of heart. Pay and enjoy your food.
Very tasty pad see ew. My wife likes that pad Thai. I would recommend people giving this a try! Pho's does a great job of providing levels of spiciness as well!
Very very good😁😁😁
The best Pad Thai in the city!

Delicious food and very quick! They got my order wrong but quickly sent over the correct food, let me keep the wrong food and threw in a free drink! Staff was very friendly about the whole deal. Will definitely order from again.
I ordered for delivery Chicken Pad Thai lunch special. It didn't taste fresh. The noodles were over cooked and the chicken didn't taste good. I couldn't eat it.
Friendly, delicious Thai spot with as much spice as you can handle. We usually do “mild plus” which is plenty spicy.

Love this place! Small but bursting with LARGE flavors.. If you like spicy then this place is it. I prefer hotX1 but I would recommend if you don't like your nose running, then just get medium. If you do anything higher than 5X, you get your picture on the wall. I love their lunch specials, portions are right where they need to be and are reasonably priced. Service is a little lack luster but truly Pho is a carry out joint..
Simple and very good. Wonderfully spicy. Fast.

My husband loved his food but they got my order wrong. I specifically asked for fried shrimp rolls and what I got was spring rolls. I understand it was specific request but the waiter made it seem like he understood and I tipped for pick up service. I have to go to bed hungry bc someone didn't listen.
Nice staff, great food. Nice location as well
Very small & quite dirty
Tom kha soup was watery, rice was under cooked and stale, thai tea was sm red watery solution, this is the worst thai food i had, will never place an order again with them.
Great if you like it hot.

I LOVE PHO'S! When I lived in the area I ordered takeout from here almost every week. Consistently great food; every dish I've had has been delicious. The mild+ spice option is my favorite. The restaurant is a cozy little BYO joint and the delivery service is really fast. The only caveat to dining in is that it can get cold in the winter when people are walking in and out, since it's such a small space. But it's well worth it to watch the chefs make the crab Rangoon by hand!
Good food. Small space. Door doesn't close completely so it was very cold... seems like an easy fix so I don't know why they haven't done so.
Best "Musman" / "Massaman" curry I've had in Chicago, maybe ever. Their spice levels are a bit elevated. I eat spicy things a lot and medium was a perfect spice level.
Best spicy Thai food in Chicago!
Best Thai food restaurant in Chicago period. I wonder how they get it soo right. Food is delicious and has the best Thai flavors. Thanks so much for operating.
Never seen a restaurant that doesn’t allow dine in 25 mins before closing. Either you close at 9:30 or 10. Pick one and stick to it.
Hands down my favorite Thai place in the area. They don't take it easy on the spice which I love. The prices of entrees are fair and their appetizers are cheap.

Total hole in the wall with some of the best, most authentic Thai food I've had in Chicago. I cannot recommend the Pad See Eiw any higher, but be careful of the spice levels! Only done carry-out, but the food was ready very quickly and a very reasonable price.

There's not a lot of space here, but the service and food make up for any cramped eating. SO GOOD. I judge all Thai by the quality of the Pad Thai, and this was almost on par with the best I've ever had.
If you like spicy flavorful thai, this is the place for you
This place is awesome!  I'm a Thai food(Asian food in general) junkie and just popped in here from out of town.  Very impressed.  Great lunch special and great flavor in everything.
Great thai food! I even did the spicy challenge at level five. Regretted strongly, but it really helps to have chocolates on hand during and ice cream after. I survived. Definitely a buy!
Holy fast delivery! Great food for late late nights, after a few drinks.
Authentic thai food. Quite spicy
Tasty
Enjoyed it. I love hot and spicy but even I was overwhelmed. Be forewarned.
Man, this place is great. Be warned on the spice. It's no joke here. Hot is absolutely fire.  Though no sauce based dishes will be less spicy than the sauce based ones.
Ordered delivery: food came quickly, in large proportions, was delicious, and very reasonably priced. Will definitely order delivery again!
The duck red curry was scrumptious, but I'll be ordering take out not dining in next time.
Tiny place, very reasonably priced with excellent Thai food. When you ask for hot food, you will get hot food, which is rare for the Midwest and made me very happy. We will be back.
Some of the best Thai fast food in Chicago.  Be careful with the spice levels though.  Their medium is actually hot, and their hot is actually super-hot.
Spicy as hell. Couldn't take this awesome.
Delicious Thai food at very good price! the spice in the food is great, and you can decide how hot you make it!
Very delicious. Great flavor. Medium was good for me and I'm normally a hot.

My fav Thai place in the Chicago area. Be careful of their spice level. Medium is spicy. Go for the mild plus first before trying anything spicier unless you really like spicy. It is BYOB so that is another plus. Their lunch specials are a great deal, meal comes with rice, soup, and a wonton usually.
If they could get their spiciness measures straight, this place would be great.  Love the heat and authenticity of the food.
Great thai food. Love that they duo not shy away from the heat levels. The pad khee mao is killer here.

I love Thai food. I found this place about 3 years ago. This is my favorite restaurant to get a good, fresh and great tasting meal, fast.  Love the gentlemen that  work there.  Just always a good experience and great food at a great price.

Honestly one of the worst dining experiences I've ever had. Appetizers & entrees came out before our drinks, I had to ask for them. My friends had their food for 10 minutes before I finally asked if mine would be ready soon, 5 minutes later they brought it over, cold, like it was sitting to the side, forgotten about. We waited even longer for our check and asked for it numerous times. Still sitting here, actually. Food is mediocre, service is god awful. I will never come here again. It is absolutely ridiculous. I do not know how they have any customers, especially for dine in.

So date night Friday turned out to be a cycling adventure. In short, considering it's been well over a year since I cycled, I didn't want to cycle any further up north from our starting point downtown, so I was happy Pho's Spicier Thai was our option to stop in this area. This was my first time here. After buying some much needed cold brews across the street, we sat down at our table where we were greeted right away with some menus.  It's small and quaint, and the wall is decorated with pictures of people that have taken up their spice challenges. My date and I immediately decided we didn't want to take part lol, so our meal choices were as far from spice as possible.  We started with the fresh spring rolls, which were just okay to me. The rolls were a little dry for my liking. For our entrees, my date ordered the Musman curry and I went with the Pad Woon Sen noodles, both with tofu, and both which we shared.  The Musman Curry was awesome! Seriously flavorful. My Pad Woon Sen noodles were also pretty good, but nothing amazing.  The service was great. The staff were all super nice. They were on it with the water refills, and they checked up on us often to make sure we were ok.  All in all, a great place for some quick Thai food.
Great food
Pho..Gross no flavor.. just a waste of money. Worst i ever had
We had seafood curry it was amazing! Tom kha was some of the best ive ever had!  Service and everything was so great!
Not bad. But not great. And they forgot my rice.
Great place. Beware the spice level... This place certainly brings the heat!
The foods is delicious! The delivery was very fast and friendly. I recommend this place to anyone. I personally love basil fried rice, egg roll, pad thai.
Simply perfect. Don't change!
Best Thai in Chicago

This is one of my favorite Thai restaurants in Chicago the food is phenomenal I don't know what it is exactly but the texture of the rice the ingredients the flavors they're just mouth watering the protein the use like the chicken/steak just are really fresh. I totally recommend this place if you're looking for great Thai food
Best Thai food in the city and definitely flavorful spice.... Yum

Disappointing after reading all the reviews. Good but not outstanding. It would be helpful if they had a description of their heat numbers somewhere. Is it a secret club thing? I also appreciate servers who recommend dishes. You're on your own here. I'll give the place one more try.
Best Thai in the area. If you order online you get a 10% off your order!

Hole-in-the-wall BYOB type restaurant with some of the most delicious curry I have ever had the fortune of tasting. Highly recommend both Panang and Red curries!!! One word of caution, if you say you want the dish hot they will ask you "Are you sure?". If you answer yes, prepare your taste buds, because you will get Thai hot, which is significantly more intense than American hot.  Can't recommend this place enough!
Best Thai I've had in 42 years of life!!!
As hot as you can handle.

What a hidden gem - this place is phenomenal. Spicy! Order a spice level below what you normally get, because they really know how to bring the heat. I frequently order thai food "as hot as you can make it," but Pho's Medium spice is more than satisfactory to me.
The bowl of soup I got to go was only 3/4 full and they didn't even put a spoon in the bag! I'll go to the other Thai place a block away from now on

We ordered the Panang Curry with tofu for takeout.  The service was fast and friendly, and the food was delicious! The curry had a prominent lemon grass tang that helped to cut through the rich savoriness of the peanut sauce.

Pho's Hot and Spicy Thai is a hidden gem in West Lakeview, serving some of the spiciest and most delicious Thai cuisine around. The restaurant is very small and personal, the whole dining area is limited to about 6 tables, and is usually staffed by just a cook and waitress. The staff is very friendly and fast, and the food is consistently delicious. Also, the meals are very reasonably priced, the lunch specials typically cost about $7.  If your feeling bold, you can try to do one of Pho's spicy challenges, anything over 2X spicy gets you on the wall of fame and your meal is free. Be warned, its not for the faint of tongue!

A small hole in the wall place with only a few tables, but amazing food. The best thai food I have had in Chicago with out a doubt. The food in SPICY beware, but worth it. It is not expensive and BYOB.
Best Thai food in Chicago! I love this place!
The best Thai food I have ever had.  We eat thai food fequently, but this one really takes the cheese.  Watch out for the spice level though.  Medium is really hot, hot is like death ... yummmm

This place is a great place for authentic thai food.  It's a very small restaurant, but the food is delicious.  The best thing about this place is the amount of spice in their foods.  I love spicy food - and they definitely make it spicy for you.  What's awesome is that you can customize the heat in each dish... and they actually do it.  I've been to many restaurants where the "hot"... really isn't that hot.  Here you can get "hot" or "xtra hot" or "2x" or on and on! Love this place.  Definitely my go to Thai place in the city now!

This place is great, its real small but the food is just what it should be. Not afraid of getting food poisoning here unlike done other thai food places in chicago. Service is good, and cant beat the lunch special.
Most authentic Thai food in the city
